<div id="review_3144902106" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3144902106" />
    <a title="Rianne Werring" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31144018-rianne-werring"><img alt="Rianne Werring" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1399372609p2/31144018.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3144902106?book_show_action=true">Apr 01, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rianne Werring" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rianne Werring" href="/user/show/31144018-rianne-werring">Rianne Werring</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3144902106" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2873498859223422907">Should you be willing to subject yourself to the sweet torture which reading this novel entails; reader, beware! It is no easy feat. This book is heavy enough in matter and form to kill a man. It is slow and thicker than quicksand, dreary and fantastical. <br/>But it is also a wonderfully intriguing document for anyone interested in medieval literature, a true relic of early European customs, manner and language. This should be your motivation for picking up this book, and not a quest for entertainme</span>
  <span id="freeText2873498859223422907" style="display:none">Should you be willing to subject yourself to the sweet torture which reading this novel entails; reader, beware! It is no easy feat. This book is heavy enough in matter and form to kill a man. It is slow and thicker than quicksand, dreary and fantastical. <br />But it is also a wonderfully intriguing document for anyone interested in medieval literature, a true relic of early European customs, manner and language. This should be your motivation for picking up this book, and not a quest for entertainment. Then you may withstand it and, God willing, even enjoy it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2873498859223422907" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


