<span id="freeTextContainer3029462967479375080">This book has a bit of all genres it seems. A bit of the comic, the tragic, the dramatic, the fantastical, the romantic and a tiny bit of suspense.<br/><br/>Although the book is over 500 years old, some things don&apos;t much change. Men still want to have their women before they marry them... That Tirant Lo Blanc is encouraged and gets to have his girlfriend in her bed before they are married, kind of disappoints me from an otherwise very devotely Catholic story/book.<br/><br/>Anyhow, I did enjoy the story. :)</span>
