    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer969204545" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1683803494361125291">Ugh. This has to be the worst Chivalric romance I&apos;ve ever read - well tried to read anyway. It&apos;s those morals of the times, which I usually understand as just that, but x30. Not really enjoyable in any way and I think I&apos;ll risk reading Don Q without this one finished. On to Orlando Furioso which is hopefully better and then, Don Q here I come!<br/><br/>-------------<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>Could only get a free ebook version if I didn&apos;t want to pay a load of money. It&apos;s for some reasons only divided into four chapters with the la</span>
  <span id="freeText1683803494361125291" style="display:none">Ugh. This has to be the worst Chivalric romance I've ever read - well tried to read anyway. It's those morals of the times, which I usually understand as just that, but x30. Not really enjoyable in any way and I think I'll risk reading Don Q without this one finished. On to Orlando Furioso which is hopefully better and then, Don Q here I come!<br /><br />-------------<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Could only get a free ebook version if I didn't want to pay a load of money. It's for some reasons only divided into four chapters with the last one being exceptionally long. It's 400 and something pages and yet I'm still wondering if this is abridged or not?<br /><br />Ah well, I've finished the first chapter and so far it's not really doing it for me, so an abridged version wouldn't annoy me too much. I'll take what I can get with these important, yet somehow obscure chivalric romances. I do NOT want to spend a fortune on them, just to understand Don Q better, if a cheap or free abridged version will do fine!</span>
